title: shellphp
extract: Definition of mollusk. : any of a large phylum (Mollusca) of invertebrate animals (such as snails, clams, or squids) with a soft unsegmented body usually enclosed in a calcareous shell broadly : shellfish. Other Words from mollusk Example Sentences Learn More about mollusk.
